<br>
a) Advertising of non-Paladin, non-EQ related material. Posting links to 'fun' stuff is ok, this is in regards blatant advertising.<br>
<br>
b) Spamming.<br>
<br>
c) Posting Offensive material. (pornography etc)<br>
<br>
d) Excess Profanity. A little minor swearing to make a point is acceptable, Profanity for the sake of Profanity is not.<br>
<br>
e) Personal Attacks. You can attack what someone has to say, but you cannot attack the person saying it.<br>
<br>
an example:<br>
<br>
&quot;What a stupid thing to say!&quot; is ok.<br>
&quot;You are stupid&quot; is not.<br>
<br>
f) Flaming. (attacking someone just for the sake of it, without a justifiable reason)<br>
<br>
g) Trolling. (posting a deliberately inflamatory comment with the intent of annoying others)<br>
<br>
<br>
2) The following are very frowned upon. (will get your post edited/deleted and a telling off from the moderators)<br>
<br>
a) Posting to the wrong forum. We have a number of different forums for a reason. Please post in the correct place.<br>
<br>
b) Cross Posting. Never post the same thing in more than 1 forum.<br>
<br>
c) Violation of the signature rules.<br>
<br>
d) Posting all in capitals. Especially thread titles. Threads all in caps WILL be deleted.<br>
<br>
3) Signatures must be kept below 50kb in size. Flash/shockwave animations are allowed, as long as they are below this size. Remember, not everyone is on broadband.<br>
<br>
4) Scripts that produce 'mouse-over' graphical effects on images in signatures are not allowed, as they have been proven to cause problems for some users.<br>
<br>
5) A signature should be no deeper than 10 lines of text, including images, and should not be so wide as to cause the window to extend on a 800x600 display.<br>
<br>
6) Under no circumstance should sound be included in any thread, and this includes signatures.<br>
<br>
Continued violations of rules in the above section can and will result in a warning, and possibly a ban.<br>
<br>
The main rule is this:<br>
<br>
Remember this is a game that we play to have fun. Posting here should be just as enjoyable for all users, as playing EQ<br>
